<br>
1) Raid with one of the Guilds on the rotation to build merit. I don't see why this one is such a big deal; granted you probly arent going to get a VS stone the first time you raid VS, but were you really expecting one? Most Guilds on the rotation raid serveral things serveral times a week; it really isnt that hard to make yourself involved. You might even make some friends =)<br>
<br>
2) Ask nicely. I don't see what is so hard about this one either. I don't understand why alot of people read &quot;ask nicely&quot; and see &quot;kiss ass&quot;.  For gods sake, one or two of the Guilds on the rotation have pretty much done everything but come out and say, &quot;just ask nice and we'll give you a stone&quot;. <br>
<br>
3) Ok so you have no merit with any of these guilds, you have not interest in building merit with any of these guilds, and you have tried asking nicely but it just didnt work for you. Offer to purchace one via multi quest. Honestly rangers...ask your self this: If FBSS's are sold commonly for 8-10k in ec, how is 20k for an item with double the haste value? Seems pretty fair to me. Especialy considering that inferieour haste items (such as rbg, etc) routinely sell for more than 20k.<br>
<br>
4) Assemble an alliance that is capable of taking VS and ask (again, ask nicely lol) to join the rotation. While this one is probably the most diffcult of the three, no one is stopping you from doing this.<br>
<br>
I really think it is nice of you to try to sort this out for people Pet, but I think people's options are fairly clear. Especialy if VS is now a twice a week spawn, I think this will become a non issue fairly quickly.<br>
